<item>
            <title>[LU-412] auster found /usr/sbin/lfsck instead of lfsck.sh</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-412</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;auster looks for test scripts like this:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;run_suite_logged() {
    # ...
    suite_script=$(find_script_in_path $suite_name $PATH:$LUSTRE/tests)
    # ...
}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;When I was trying to run the &quot;lfsck&quot; test script, suite_name was &quot;lfsck&quot;, and /usr/sbin/lfsck was found, instead of lfsck.sh in the test script directory.  This issue also caused sgpdd-survey and obdfilter-survey to fail.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
